Help Type: topic
Topic: recipe

Workflow Recipe

Purpose:
  Read this after root help. It is the practical workflow guide for Agents and users operating `.wikg` archives.
  It explains what to try first, which objects matter, when to inspect jobs or index state, and where detailed rules live.

Primary contract:
  - Use Wiki Graph URIs as stable object handles.
  - If you have a URI and need valid operations, run `wikigraph <uri> --help`.
  - If you need concrete predicate usage for that URI type, run `wikigraph <uri> <predicate> --help`.
  - Never pass a bare filesystem path to URI-targeted commands.
    /Users/me/book.wikg -> wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg
    ./book.wikg -> wikg://book.wikg
  - Treat returned short URIs as archive-relative handles. Add the archive locator before passing them back:
    wikg://entity/Q8018 -> wikg:///absolute/path/book.wikg/entity/Q8018

Normal workflow:
  1. Create or import an archive.
     wikigraph wikg://book.wikg create ./book.epub
     wikigraph wikg://notes.wikg create ./notes.md
     cat article.md | wikigraph wikg://article.wikg create --input-format markdown

  2. Inspect unfamiliar archives before retrieval.
     wikigraph wikg://book.wikg inspect
     Use inspect to learn chapter structure, generated data readiness, index state, and suggested next commands.

  3. Search with a scope URI.
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg --query "恩典 婴儿洗礼"
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/chapter/3 --query "婴儿洗礼"
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity --query "朱元璋"

  4. Open the returned object URI.
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/chunk/123
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity/Q162593
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/triple/Q162593/discusses/Q9476

  5. Ground, expand, or pack an object.
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 evidence
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 related --evidence 2
     wikigraph wikg:///Users/me/book.wikg/entity/Q162593 pack --budget 5000

  6. Continue paged output when needed.
     wikigraph next <cursor>

  7. Export a ready archive.
     wikigraph wikg://book.wikg export --output-format markdown --output out.md

Object choices:
  - Use `chapter` when you need structure, readiness, source boundaries, or chapter-local search.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3

  - Use `chunk` when you need source-backed passages and local reading context.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chunk
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chunk/123 evidence

  - Use `entity` when the question is about a concept, person, place, term, or object that may have aliases or variants.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018 evidence
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018 related --query "aspect"

  - Use `triple` when the question is about a relation or claim between two graph objects.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/triple/Q8018/discusses/Q123 evidence

  - Use `summary` when you need compressed reading output before going back to source evidence.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3/summary

Retrieval strategy:
  - Start with inspect when the archive is unknown.
  - Use the narrowest scope that can still answer the question.
  - Use source search for literal wording.
  - Use entity evidence for known entities; do not rely on label text search as the primary path.
  - Use `related` to expand from a chunk or entity.
  - Use `pack` only after choosing a located chunk or entity URI.
  - Use `--context 0` when exact cited ranges matter; otherwise keep the default source context.

Index awareness:
  Search, evidence, and related depend on available index and generated data.
  If retrieval is empty or inspect reports missing search support, inspect first and then use index help for the exact operation:
    wikigraph <archive-uri> inspect
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index --help
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/index build --help

Job awareness:
  Reading Graph, Reading Summary, and Knowledge Graph generation are lower-frequency operations, but missing generated data can block normal retrieval.
  Inspect before starting expensive work. Jobs call an LLM, consume tokens, and may run for minutes to hours.
    wikigraph wikg://local/job
    wikigraph wikg://local/job add --input <chapter-uri> --task reading-graph --accept-cost
    wikigraph wikg://local/job/<job-id> watch --jsonl

Configuration path:
  Configure local LLM and provider settings through config URIs.
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm set --json '{"provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1"}'
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm put apiKey --secret
    wikigraph wikg://local/config/llm test

Maintenance path:
  Use maintenance commands when you are intentionally editing archive content or metadata.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter add --stage source --title "Chapter 1" --input ./chapter.md --input-format markdown
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3/source set --input ./chapter.md --input-format markdown
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/chapter/3/title set "New title"
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg/entity/Q8018/meta

Format path:
  Use `create` to make or import a managed archive, `export` to project from it, and `transform` for one-shot conversion without keeping an archive.
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg create ./book.epub
    wikigraph wikg://book.wikg export --output-format markdown --output out.md
    cat chapter.txt | wikigraph transform --input-format txt --output-format markdown

